  "text": "16 A more general approach, not yet implemented, but which removes the restriction that the protected subsystems be hierarchical, is described by Schroeder in his doctoral thesis [CITATION_1] . does not need to take the fact that he is calling a protected subsystem into account when he tries to estimate the performance of a new program design. 2. It is quite easy to extend to the user the ability to write protected subsystems of his own. Without any special privileges, any user may develop his own proprietary program, data-screening system, or extra authentication system, and be assured that even though he permits others to use his protected subsystem, the information he is protecting receives the same kind of security as does the supervisor itself.",
